# moonBASIC workspace

- **Default `go run .` / `go build .`** (no tags) = **compiler only**. It writes `.mbc`; it does **not** run a graphical game. Full games need **`-tags fullruntime`** and **`cmd/moonrun`** or **`moonbasic --run`** (see `docs/DEVELOPER.md`).
- **`compiler/builtinmanifest/commands.json`** defines user-visible command names and arities. After editing it, run `go run . --check` on a representative `.mb` sample; refresh `docs/API_CONSISTENCY.md` with `go run ./tools/apidoc` when the public API changes.
- **Runtime work** lives under `runtime/`; **bytecode / VM** under `vm/`; **language front-end** under `compiler/`.
- For contributor commands and CI parity: `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `docs/DEVELOPER.md`, `AGENTS.md`.
